## Viking-UI component law (non-negotiable)

### Angular (`deml.app`, `viking-ui`, `viking-ui-showcase`)

- **Always** import and use components from `@dataengineeringformachinelearning/viking-ui`.
- **Never** add Angular Material, ng-zorro, PrimeNG, Bootstrap, shadcn runtimes, or other third-party UI kits.
- **Never** create one-off styled buttons, inputs, modals, toasts, tables, or charts when a `viking-*` component exists.
- **Prefer** shell primitives: `viking-app-header`, `viking-app-sidebar`, `viking-page-header`, `viking-footer`, `viking-site-navbar`, `viking-site-footer`.
- **Compose** page layouts with `viking-page-shell`, `viking-section`, `viking-panel-grid`, `viking-form-grid`, `viking-stack`, and `viking-cluster`; use lower-level `viking-grid` only for content-led or deliberately unequal 12-track layouts. Static surfaces use their matching package CSS classes.
- **Choose layouts by intent:** peer cards/charts/HUD panels use `viking-panel-grid`; field groups use `viking-form-grid`; consecutive blocks use `viking-stack`; repeated title/description/action/body anatomy uses `viking-section-template`. Never reproduce those contracts with app-specific classes, sibling margins, alignment overrides, or repeated header markup.
- **Charts:** `viking-chart` (native SVG) only — no ApexCharts, Chart.js, D3 wrappers, or canvas libs. Always use `viking-chart-panel` as the chart container with `viking-chart-panel[loading]` and `viking-chart-empty-state` for all states. Import `VIKING_SERIES_PRESETS` from `series-presets.ts` for series colors — never raw hex.
- **Icons:** `viking-icon` only — no Material Icons, Font Awesome, or Lucide runtime packages.
- **Feedback:** `viking-toast` / `VikingToastService`, `viking-callout`, `viking-badge` — not browser `alert()` or ad-hoc banners.
- **Loading:** `viking-skeleton`, `viking-loading-overlay`, `viking-progress` — not generic spinners or CSS-only loaders.
- **Framework-neutral shared UI** (styles, primitives, services, utilities) belongs in `packages/viking-ui/` first.
- `packages/viking-ui/` is the single home for all Viking-UI code, including token SCSS, static CSS bundles, Web Components, Angular-free utility exports, package metadata, and all Angular wrapper components.
- Do not add `styleUrl`, `styleUrls`, inline `styles`, or component-local SCSS to Angular app components. If a visual rule is needed, create or extend a Viking-UI component. Angular component files must not contain any visual styling — all rules belong in the Viking-UI package.
- Never import from private package internals (`packages/viking-ui/src/...`) in app/runtime code. Consume public entrypoints through the npm package or workspace alias: package root or `/angular` for Angular, `/web-components.js` for custom elements, `/icons` and `/site-drakkar` for static-site utilities, `/tokens.json` for design tooling.

```typescript
import {
  VikingButton,
  VikingCard,
  VikingField,
  VikingInput,
} from "@dataengineeringformachinelearning/viking-ui";
```

### Non-Angular (marketing Astro, Django templates, Swagger)

- Load synced CSS: `design-tokens.css` + `viking-ui.css` (from `scripts/sync_design_system.py`).
- Use `@dataengineeringformachinelearning/viking-ui/icons`, `@dataengineeringformachinelearning/viking-ui/site-drakkar`, `@dataengineeringformachinelearning/viking-ui/tokens.json`, and `@dataengineeringformachinelearning/viking-ui/manifest` for build-time/static-site data. Do not pull the Angular barrel into Astro prerender paths.
- Prefer jsDelivr CDN URLs for package-hosted static artifacts when a surface can safely consume CDN assets; otherwise use synced artifacts generated from `packages/viking-ui/`.
- Use semantic HTML plus documented `viking-*` components/classes from the synced Viking-UI bundle — no local `<style>` blocks, inline styles, one-off palettes, or platform-specific CSS.
- Mirror composable field ergonomics with tokenized form markup; do not embed React/Vue widget runtimes.

