## THEME.md token law (zero hardcoded styles)

### Always use tokens

- **Colors:** `--viking-*` semantic aliases (`--viking-bg`, `--viking-surface`, `--viking-accent`, `--viking-text-muted`, …). Every color resolves to a token — the only permitted hex literals live in `_variables.scss` and `_series-colors.scss`.
- **Spacing:** `--viking-space-*` on the **8px primary grid** (`--viking-space-unit`). Use integer steps only; `--viking-space-0-5` (4px) is the sole tight exception. Never invent raw px gaps.
- **Typography:** `--viking-font-family`, `--viking-font-size-*`, `--viking-font-weight-*`, `--viking-letter-spacing-*`, `--viking-line-height-*`
- **Radius:** `--viking-radius-*` (max 16px except pills). Cards: `--viking-radius-lg` (12px). Buttons: `--viking-radius` (8px).
- **Shadows:** `--viking-shadow-*` with machined top-edge highlights. Hierarchy through token stepping, never stacked opacity.
- **Motion:** `--viking-duration-*`, `--viking-ease-*`, respect `prefers-reduced-motion`
- **Charts:** `--viking-series-1` … `--viking-series-8` or `tone` props — import `VIKING_SERIES_PRESETS` from `series-presets.ts`. Never raw hex in chart code.
- **Breakpoints:** `--viking-bp-*` only (`sm: 600px`, `md: 768px`, `sidebar: 901px`, `lg: 1024px`, `xl: 1440px`, `2xl: 1920px`). Never invent ad-hoc pixel values.

### Never

- Hardcode hex/rgb/hsl (`#2176FF`, `#fff`, `rgb(17,17,17)`) in components, templates, or inline styles
- Load Inter from Google Fonts CDN — use self-hosted `_fonts.scss`
- Add gradient orbs, mesh backgrounds, neon glow, glassmorphism, or decorative clutter on base layouts
- Use emojis in product UI (exception: 🇺🇸 on approved badges only)
- Use `.viking-font-display` on body copy — CES/marketing display labels only
- Exceed `--viking-container-max-width` (1260px) without `.page-inner-wrapper` intent
- Register customer domains in static CSS/CORS — database-driven per AGENTS.md
- Use ad-hoc breakpoint pixel values (e.g., `560px`, `640px`, `820px`, `960px`, `980px`) — use `--viking-bp-*` tokens only

### Layout & aesthetic

- **Grid-first composition:** All pages compose `viking-page-shell` → `viking-section` with semantic layout recipes. Use `viking-panel-grid` for equal-height peer surfaces, `viking-form-grid` for top-aligned fields, `viking-stack` for vertical rhythm, and `viking-section-template` for repeated section anatomy. Use lower-level `viking-grid` only for content-led or deliberately unequal 12-track regions. Start as single-column grid and scale at the canonical tablet and desktop breakpoints. Application routes use `viking-app-layout` + `viking-page-template` (supports `width="narrow"`, `"default"`, `"wide"`).
- **Context-aware density:** Apply the right density for the context. Dashboards/analytics: `viking-metric-card`, `viking-hud-panel`, `viking-chart-panel` for dense data inlay. Settings/billing: `viking-form-section` with grouped `viking-field` stacks. Status/overview: open `viking-card` with generous padding. Static/marketing: wider readable widths (`--viking-content-readable-max-width`). Never force a dashboard density pattern into a settings form.
- **Tactile surfaces:** subtle inset top-edge highlights, etched steel-like borders, and 1px hover lift max.
- **Dense, breathable layout:** cards, buttons, charts, and overview panels must support Flux-like data density while using tokenized padding (`--viking-card-padding`, `--viking-panel-padding`) and exact alignment.
- **Primitive clarity:** favor spartan.ng-style clean composition and predictable controls; do not solve missing primitives with app-local CSS.
- **Mobile-first:** 44px touch targets, `--viking-space-2` gutters scaling to `--viking-space-3`.
- **Status:** never color alone — pair tone with `viking-icon`, label, or pattern.

